FBIS4-61541 "drsov089_d_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-089 Daily Report 6 May 1994 REGIONAL AFFAIRS Regions Warned Gas Supplies Will Be Cut Because of Debts Regions Warned Gas Supplies Will Be Cut Because of Debts PM0605151794 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 6 May 94 p 1 PM0605151794 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI Russian BFN [Untitled report from ITAR-TASS/INTERFAX "News in Brief" roundup] [Text] The "Gazprom" Russian Joint-Stock Company has warned the leaders of a number of Russian Federation Republics and oblasts that deliveries of natural gas for power industry facilities and industrial enterprises may be cut in the light of their indebtedness to "Gazprom." Warnings that gas deliveries will cease for various regions 4 through 9 May have been sent to Karachayevo-Cherkessia, Ingushetia, Kabardino-Balkaria, North Ossetia, Bashkiria, and Dagestan, as well as Perm, Novosibirsk, Astrakhan, Kemerovo, Rostov, and Voronezh Oblasts, and Stavropol Kray.
